35UPCEANReader::UPCEANReader(const DecodeHints& hints) :
36 _allowedExtensions(hints.allowedEanExtensions())
37{
38}

40BitArray::Range
41UPCEANReader::FindStartGuardPattern(const BitArray& row)
42{
43#if 0
44 // this is the way the upstream JAVA project implemented it: scan for a
45 // pattern 111 and look for a quite-zone of 3 after the fact. If there is no
46 // quite zone, then skip the whole pattern und start over. This fails to identify
47 // the valid start guard given the input: 49333... (falsepositives-2/14.png
48 // line 471)
49
50 BitArray::Range range{row.begin(), row.begin()};
51 while(range.end != row.end()) {
52 range = FindGuardPattern(row, range.end, false, UPCEANCommon::START_END_PATTERN.data(),
53 UPCEANCommon::START_END_PATTERN.size());
54
55 // Make sure there is a quiet zone at least as big as the start pattern before the barcode.
56 // If this check would run off the left edge of the image, do not accept this barcode,
57 // as it is very likely to be a false positive.
58 if (row.hasQuiteZone(range.begin, -range.size(), false))
59 return range;
60 }
61 return {row.end(), row.end()};
62#else
63 // this is the 'right' way to do it: scan for a pattern of the form 3111, where 3 is the quitezone
64 // note upstream uses a quite-zone width of 3 modules but the spec requires 9
65 const auto& pattern = UPCEANCommon::START_END_PATTERN;
66 using Counters = std::decay<decltype(pattern)>::type;
67 Counters counters{};
68
69 return RowReader::FindPattern(
70 row.getNextSet(row.begin()), row.end(), counters,
71 [&row, &pattern](BitArray::Iterator begin, BitArray::Iterator end, const Counters& cntrs) {
72 // Make sure there is a quiet zone at least as big as the start pattern before the barcode.
73 // If this check would run off the left edge of the image, do not accept this barcode,
74 // as it is very likely to be a false positive.
75 return row.hasQuiteZone(begin, static_cast<int>(-(end-begin)), false) &&
76 RowReader::PatternMatchVariance(cntrs, pattern, MAX_INDIVIDUAL_VARIANCE) < MAX_AVG_VARIANCE;
77 });
78#endif
79}
80
81Result
82UPCEANReader::decodeRow(int rowNumber, const BitArray& row, std::unique_ptr<DecodingState>&) const
83{
84 auto range = FindStartGuardPattern(row);
85 if (!range)
86 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
87
88 return decodeRow(rowNumber, row, range);
89}
90
91BitArray::Range
92UPCEANReader::decodeEnd(const BitArray& row, BitArray::Iterator begin) const
93{
94 BitArray::Range next = {begin, row.end()};
95 ReadGuardPattern(&next, UPCEANCommon::START_END_PATTERN);
96 return {begin, next.begin};
97}
98
99Result
100UPCEANReader::decodeRow(int rowNumber, const BitArray& row, BitArray::Range startGuard) const
101{
102 std::string result;
103 result.reserve(20);
104 auto range = decodeMiddle(row, startGuard.end, result);
105 if (!range)
106 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
107
108 auto stopGuard = decodeEnd(row, range.end);
109 if (!stopGuard)
110 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
111
112 // Make sure there is a quiet zone at least as big as the end pattern after the barcode. The
113 // spec might want more whitespace, but in practice this is the maximum we can count on.
114 if (!row.hasQuiteZone(stopGuard.end, stopGuard.size(), false))
115 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
116
117 if (!checkChecksum(result))
118 return Result(DecodeStatus::ChecksumError);
119
120 BarcodeFormat format = expectedFormat();
121 int xStart = static_cast<int>(startGuard.begin - row.begin());
122 int xStop = static_cast<int>(stopGuard.end - row.begin() - 1);
123
124 Result decodeResult(result, rowNumber, xStart, xStop, format);
125 Result extensionResult = UPCEANExtensionSupport::DecodeRow(rowNumber, row, stopGuard.end);
126 if (extensionResult.isValid())
127 {
128 decodeResult.metadata().put(ResultMetadata::UPC_EAN_EXTENSION, extensionResult.text());
129 decodeResult.metadata().putAll(extensionResult.metadata());
130 //TODO: extend position in include extension
131 //decodeResult.addResultPoints(extensionResult.resultPoints());
132 }
133
134 if (!_allowedExtensions.empty() && !Contains(_allowedExtensions, extensionResult.text().size())) {
135 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
136 }
137
138 if (format == BarcodeFormat::EAN_13 || format == BarcodeFormat::UPC_A) {
139 std::string countryID = EANManufacturerOrgSupport::LookupCountryIdentifier(result);
140 if (!countryID.empty()) {
141 decodeResult.metadata().put(ResultMetadata::POSSIBLE_COUNTRY, TextDecoder::FromLatin1(countryID));
142 }
143 }
144
145 return decodeResult;
146}
147
148/**
149* Computes the UPC/EAN checksum on a string of digits, and reports
150* whether the checksum is correct or not.
151*
152* @param s string of digits to check
153* @return true iff string of digits passes the UPC/EAN checksum algorithm
154* @throws FormatException if the string does not contain only digits
155*/
156bool
157UPCEANReader::checkChecksum(const std::string& s) const
158{
159 return UPCEANCommon::ComputeChecksum(s, 1) == s.back() - '0';
160}
